---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateLink from '../components/AffiliateLink.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'AI Website Templates: Do They Actually Work? (2025)',
  description: 'Most AI website templates are generic garbage. Here\'s what makes templates work, what doesn\'t, and how to customize AI-generated sites so they don\'t look like everyone else\'s.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['AI website templates', 'AI website builder templates', 'customizing AI websites', 'Durable templates', 'Framer templates', 'v0 templates'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#FEF9F3] py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#E07A5F] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Honest · Tested · No Hype
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        AI Website Templates: Do They Actually Work?
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        AI generates websites in seconds. But most look like generic trash. Here's what makes templates work, what doesn't, and how to not look like everyone else using the same AI builder.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: AI templates are starting points, not finished products. Use them for structure and layout, then customize heavily. If you don't customize, your site will look generic and forgettable.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Problem With AI Templates -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Why Most AI Templates Suck
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">The "Default Template" Problem</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">AI builders generate from a limited set of templates. Once you've seen 10 AI-generated sites, you've seen them all.</p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700">Same hero sections. Same color schemes. Same "modern SaaS" look with gradients and glassmorphism. Your startup doesn't stand out. It blends in.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">The Generic Content Problem</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">AI generates placeholder text that sounds like it was written by ChatGPT. Because it was.</p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700">"Transform your business with innovative solutions." "Unleash the power of cutting-edge technology." Generic buzzwords that convey nothing. Users bounce because there's no substance.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">The Cookie-Cutter Layout Problem</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Hero section with left text/right image. Three feature cards. Testimonials. Pricing table. Footer.</p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700">This structure works, which is why everyone uses it. But it's also forgettable. When your site looks like 100 others, why would anyone remember you?</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What AI Templates Are Good For -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What AI Templates Actually Do Well
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Fast Structure</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">AI nails the basic page structure in seconds. Header, hero, features, social proof, CTA, footer.</p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700">This would take you hours to build from scratch. AI gives you a working foundation immediately. That's genuine value.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Responsive Design</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">AI templates work on mobile. No broken layouts. No weird scaling issues.</p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700">Responsive design used to take days of testing and tweaking. AI gets it right out of the box. That's massive time saved.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Accessibility Basics</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">AI templates generally follow accessibility guidelines. Proper heading hierarchy. Readable contrast. Keyboard navigation works.</p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700">Not perfect accessibility, but better than most hand-coded sites from non-experts.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How to Customize AI Templates -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      How to Make AI Templates Not Suck
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">1. Replace Every Image</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">AI uses stock photos that appear on hundreds of sites. Your startup shouldn't look like a generic template.</p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700">What to use instead:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Real product screenshots (not mockups, actual UI)</li>
          <li>• Photos of your team/workspace (authentic, not staged)</li>
          <li>• Custom illustrations (hire someone, use AI tools, or learn basic design)</li>
          <li>• Graphs/charts showing real data (not fake stats)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">2. Customize the Color Palette</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Default blues and purples are everywhere. Your brand needs distinctive colors.</p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700">How to pick colors that work:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Pick ONE primary color that reflects your brand (not blue because everyone uses blue)</li>
          <li>• Use a tool like Coolors.co to generate matching palettes</li>
          <li>• Test contrast ratios (WebAIM contrast checker) — accessibility matters</li>
          <li>• Apply colors consistently but sparingly — don't paint everything in your brand color</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">3. Rewrite Every Word</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">AI-generated copy is generic. Your copy should sound like you, not ChatGPT.</p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700">What makes copy authentic:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Specific examples instead of vague claims ("Helped 50 companies save 10 hours/week" not "Boost productivity")</li>
          <li>• Your actual voice and opinions (boring is better than fake-exciting)</li>
          <li>• Real customer quotes with names and photos (not generic testimonials)</li>
          <li>• Acknowledging what your product DOESN'T do (builds trust through honesty)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-orange-50 border-2 border-orange-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">4. Break the Layout Patterns</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Hero-left-content-right is the default. Do something different.</p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700">Ways to stand out without being weird:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Center your hero content with a large, bold headline (not generic, specific)</li>
          <li>• Use a video demo instead of a static hero image</li>
          <li>• Start with a question or statement that makes visitors think</li>
          <li>• Put features side-by-side with scroll-triggered animations (subtle, not cheesy)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">5. Add Micro-Interactions</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Static sites feel dead. Small interactions make it feel alive.</p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700">Examples of micro-interactions that work:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Hover states on buttons (color change, slight lift, shadow)</li>
          <li>• Scroll-triggered fade-ins for content sections</li>
          <li>• Smooth page transitions (not jarring, just gentle)</li>
          <li>• Interactive elements that respond to user input (toggle switches, animated counters)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Tool-Specific Template Advice -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Template Tips by AI Builder
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3"><AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink> Templates</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Durable generates full websites in 30 seconds. The templates are service-business focused (cleaning, landscaping, consulting).</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Customization priority: Replace the generic service descriptions with your specific offerings. Add real photos of your work. Durable's copy is particularly generic — rewrite everything.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3"><AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink> Templates</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">v0 generates React components using Shadcn UI. The templates are developer-focused and more technical.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Customization priority: v0's strength is the code quality, not visual design. You'll likely need to style components yourself. Use v0 for structure, then customize CSS heavily for branding.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3"><AffiliateLink href="https://framer.com">Framer</AffiliateLink> Templates</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Framer has a template marketplace with both free and paid options. Quality varies significantly.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Customization priority: Framer templates are the most customizable. Use the visual editor to change layouts, not just colors. But remember — popular templates = many sites using them. Customization is mandatory.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Relume Templates (Webflow/Figma)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Relume offers component libraries for Webflow and Figma. Not AI-generated, but worth mentioning.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Customization priority: Relume components are higher quality than most AI-generated templates. They're a better starting point if you're comfortable with Webflow or Figma. Still needs branding customization.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">The Bottom Line</h2>
      
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">AI templates get you 80% of the way there in seconds. The last 20% — customization, branding, authentic content — is what makes your site memorable.</p>
      
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Use AI templates for:</p>
      
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-6">
        <li>• Fast initial structure (hours → minutes)</li>
        <li>• Responsive design that works</li>
        <li>• Accessibility basics covered</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Then customize:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-6">
        <li>• Replace every image with real content</li>
        <li>• Customize the color palette to your brand</li>
        <li>• Rewrite every word to sound like you</li>
        <li>• Break layout patterns to stand out</li>
        <li>• Add micro-interactions for polish</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">The 80/20 rule applies: AI gets you to 80% fast. The last 20% is manual work that makes it yours. Skip the customization and your site will look like everyone else's.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related AI Website Guides
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/durable-vs-v0-vs-framer" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Durable vs v0 vs Framer</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Top AI builders compared</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/how-to-choose-ai-website-builder" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">How to Choose an AI Website Builder</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Decision framework</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
